


monit - > shows the status of the running process
monit summary -> confirms whether tomcat is running
netstat-> command line tool that displays network connections(both incoming & outgoing)
netstat -l -> shows the list of the processes listening
netstat -s -> shows the statistics of the protocols
netstat -an | grep 'LISTEN' -> greps the listening status
ps -ef | grep 'tomcat' -> 
	1. ps(list all processes)
	2. -e (list all the process irrelevant of the user)
	3. -f (show processes in full format (more detailed than default)
